The paper focuses on modeling social networks and analyzing their hierarchical structure, which falls under the scope of social network analysis and data mining. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses algorithms and graph theory, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper mentions applications related to web search and information flow, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
